      },
      "date": "2016-06-16 21:24:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2\n\nStrictly speaking, the DEGRADED OST should only be skipped if there are enough other non-DEGRADED OSTs available to meet the stripe requirements.  However, since lod_alloc_qos() will fall back to lod_alloc_rr() and this correctly includes DEGRADED OSTs when there aren't enough other OSTs, this is OK.\n\nIdeally, someone would work on LU-9 and make a single round-robin allocator that takes space balance into account, instead of jumping to random QOS allocation...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
